  <bioghist id="aspace_ff4e159ec03ba32e79a1dd27f7a92469">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Dorothy Lobrano (Mrs. Raymond C.) Guth is the daughter of long-time (1938-1956) New Yorker fiction editor, Gus Lobrano (Class of 1924) and the goddaughter of E. B. White. In 1976, she collected and edited an edition of the Letters of E. B. White.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_2c1ac768ea75caf444f8c65b49a14c60">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Letters, manuscripts, galley proofs, and other materials relating to the publication of the Letters of E. B. White. Includes numerous letters from White to Guth.</p>  </scopecontent>
